  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "That is, NN models get trained without knowing the relationship between input features and outputs.",
    "So, if many irrelevant features are used to train the NN model, it results in inaccurate prediction in testing.",
    "To address this challenge, Kim and Kang 21 have employed two preprocessing steps before applying ANN.",
    "The first step is the feature selection step to select the features based on ranking.",
    "Then, feature correlation analysis is performed to make the system learns about the correlation between feature relations and NN output thereby eliminating the black-box nature."
  ],
